  "body": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP-2369\r\n\r\n**Major Change#1**\r\n_Current behaviour:_\r\nThe client would do nothing on server initiated `Channel` close (applicable for cases when there were no active requests on the channel). This means that although the underlying `Channel`, a `Connection` would not be removed from the `ConnectionPool`. This would cause the load balancing logic to allocate a new request to a `Connection` which is already closed.\r\n\r\n_New behaviour:_\r\nWith this change, we introduce a callback on `Channel` close which would remove the connection from the `ConnectionPool` and destroy it. This would ensure that any new request would not be assigned to the already closed `Channel`.\r\n\r\n**Major Change#2**\r\n_Current behaviour:_\r\nOn failure of a request, we try to replaced the `Connection` from the `ConnectionPool`. If the `Connection` is dead, this attempt is done once per request. Since multiple requests can be assigned on the same `Connection`, the replace logic is called multiple times leading to multiple calls for new `Connection` creation even though only one `Connection` was impacted. \r\n\r\n_New behaviour:_\r\nWith this change, we introduce a new lock on Connection which will ensure that replacement of a `Connection` is done only once.\r\n\r\n**Testing**\r\n- Added tests which fail before the fixes and then succeed after the changes.\r\n- Ran `mvn clean install -DskipIntegrationTests=false` locally for gremlin-server and gremlin-driver\r\n- All integ tests pass. \r\n- Fixed some integ tests where we weren't closing the client properly after the test has ended.\r\n\r\n**Deployment plan**\r\n- Merge to 3.4-dev branch first and then merge 3.4-dev to master.\r\n- Changelog has been updated.",
